<p id="notice"><%= notice %></p>

<h1>Listing Questions</h1>

<div class="alert alert-success alert-dismissable"><button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="alert" aria-hidden="true">Ã—</button>
  <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-2">
          <h3 style="color:blue;">Questions, Setting Variables</h3>
          <div class="list-group list-group-item-default">
             <strong>
             <p>You may set questions to be answered for each customer here.
                Questions can be set targeting one of four categories:
                Demographic, Financial, Control Questions, and Macroeconomic questions.
                A question can be selected to set the value of a corresponding variable. 
                Each variable can be locked i.e. it depends on other variables that have to be set first.
                Or, unlocked, meaning it can be set right away without depending on another variable being set first.
                To manage variables, click on <a href="/variables">Manage Variables</a>
             </p>
            </strong>
          </div>
        </div>
  </div>
</div>

<ul class="list-group">
  <% @questions.each do |question| %>
    
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3">
        <div class="list-group">
          <a href="/questions/<%= question.id %>" class="list-group-item list-group-item-info">
            Question: <span class="list-group-item list-group-item-danger"><%= question.body %></span>
            Category: <span class="list-group-item list-group-item-info"><%= question.category.try(:category_name) %></span>
            Time Interval, in months: <span class="list-group-item list-group-item-warning"><%= question.interval %></span>
            Default Answer: <span class="list-group-item list-group-item-warning"><%= question.default_answer %></span>
          </a>       
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  <% end %>

</ul>

<br>

<%= link_to 'New Question', new_question_path, class: "btn btn-raised btn-primary" %>



